<h1>{{ heading }}</h1>

<p>
    In particular page setups, sticky headers can be hidden by other page
    elements implementing a similar behaviour. In this website, default sticky
    headers are hidden by the header at the top of the page. This is an example
    showing how to override the default <code>sticky</code> CSS class used to
    create sticky headers.
</p>

<div class="alert alert-info" role="alert">
